                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14473360" author="chanwit" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 09:37:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To reproduce, simply call&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;$ groovyc GreetingActor.groovy&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14473487" author="melix" created="Thu, 22 Nov 2012 08:01:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are two problems in one here:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;first, &apos;log&apos; is a generated field which is marked as synthetic, and we do not generate bridge methods for synthetic fields&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;second, &apos;log&apos; is used in a closure, which is not an inner class at the phase the static compilation visitor is run, so bridge methods are not generated at all&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Fixing this requires a rework on how we keep track of private field and private method calls from inner classes or closures.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14473501" author="melix" created="Wed, 28 Nov 2012 07:41:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Solved by having the type checker track access to private fields/methods, then the static compiler will only generate bridges for those fields/methods.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As it is a change in the way bridges are created, I will not port it to &lt;tt&gt;2.0.6&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
